Module org.postgresql.pljava.internal
Package org.postgresql.pljava.jdbc

Class SQLXMLImpl.StAXUnwrapFilter

java.lang.Object
javax.xml.stream.util.StreamReaderDelegate
org.postgresql.pljava.jdbc.SQLXMLImpl.StAXUnwrapFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
XMLStreamConstants, XMLStreamReader
Enclosing class:
SQLXMLImpl<V extends Datum>
static class SQLXMLImpl.StAXUnwrapFilter extends StreamReaderDelegate
Class to wrap an XMLStreamReader and pass all of the parse events except the outermost ("document root") element, in effect producing XML(CONTENT) when the underlying stream has had a synthetic root element wrapped around it to satisfy a JRE-bundled parser that only accepts XML(DOCUMENT).

The result may be surprising to code consuming the StAX stream, depending on what it expects; testing has shown the JRE-bundled identity transformer does not faithfully reproduce such input (though, oddly, the 'same' identity transformer reading the 'same' content through the SAXUnwrapFilter does). Code that will be expected to handle XML(CONTENT) and not just XML(DOCUMENT) using this interface should be tested for correct behavior.
